org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: Filed in the United States District Court
Order Discharging Petitioner for Writ of Habeas Corpus
In the Matter of the Application of Jung Ham and Seid Yam for a Writ of Habeas Corpus,

This cause coming on to be heard on the application of the above named petitioners, Jung Ham and Seid Yam, for an order to show cause whereby a Writ of Habeas Corpus, should not issue and the Court having duly considered the same and being fully advised in the premises does find that the said petitioners, Hung Ham and Seid Yam and each of them is being unlawfully restrained of his liberty by Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration thatand the Court does further said a writ of habeas corpus should issue

p.del: ORDER that the Writ of Habeas Corpus as prayed for be and it is hereby granted and it is further
p.add: directly the Commissioner of Immigration befrore this court the said petitioners out the 6th day of Dec 1920 at 2 oclk PM for such as way no

p.del: ORDERED by the Court that the said Henry M. White Commissioner of Immigration shall forthwith release and discharge from his custody the said Jung Ham and Seid Yam and each of them,

div1.p: DONE in open court this 3 day of December,1920.
